byline.contributor: Aurelien Breeden and Elian Peltier contributed reporting.

abstract: French authorities say migrants attempting to board freight trains to Britain made at least 2,100 attempts in less than 24-hour period to enter Eurotunnel compound in Calais, France; local volunteers say there are more than 3,000 migrants in Calais, most from North Africa and Middle East, and number keeps growing.
lead_paragraph: Group after group of migrants made their way to the Eurotunnel compound in Calais overnight on Monday, climbing over fences and other barriers in a desperate bid to reach Britain.

headline.main: Hundreds of Migrants Try to Cross English Channel on Freight Trains
headline.print_headline: Hundreds of Migrants Try to Clamber Onto Trains and Cross Channel to England
